Specify Vector Autoregressive (VAR(p = 1)) Model using dynr

Source: R/fitAutoReg-model-var-p1-dynr.R
ModelVARP1Dynr.Rd

This function specifies a VAR(p = 1) model using the dynr::dynr.model() package.

Usage

ModelVARP1Dynr(data, outfile = tempfile())

Arguments

data

Numeric matrix. The time series data with dimensions t by k, where t is the number of observations and k is the number of variables.

outfile

a character string of the name of the output C script of model functions to be compiled for parameter estimation. The default is the name for a potential temporary file returned by tempfile().
